{"id": "1302381247917588640", "channel_id": "1302381247917588640", "type": 0, "author_id": "271722208840253441", "author_name": "starfish3302", "author_bot": false, "content": "Great work on the game! I especially love the characters and their personality, so I love getting extra content from the breeding frenzy event. \n\nThough I wanted to share some feedback regarding some bonus content scenes that, for some players, may feel intense or unexpected, especially when it involves interactions that are more forceful. I read Goliath's story after Aurita and it was pretty jarring and a bit off putting, but I imagine for some people they might this more seriously that intended. \n\nWould it be possible to consider adding either a small disclaimer or a warning for certain character's story, such as Goliath? Such as a small icon or just a text popup that warns the player what they are getting into and allows skipping. This way, everyone can enjoy the bonus content at their own comfort level and it doesn't take much effort to implement. \n\nThank you so much for considering this.", "timestamp": "2024-11-02T21:18:06.577000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1302381247917588640", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "suggestion regarding breeding frenzy event", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1181168158678204497"]}
